On April 23, 2018, Vice President Mike Pence spoke at NASA headquarters in Washington, D.C. to swear in Jim Bridenstine as the new Administrator of NASA. Pence commended Bridenstine's background in military service, public policy, and management, and expressed the administration's commitment to ensuring that NASA has the resources and support it needs to lead in space exploration. Bridenstine expressed his gratitude for the opportunity to serve as Administrator and highlighted the importance of NASA's work in advancing scientific knowledge and preparing for future missions to the moon and Mars. The event also included a live video call with astronauts on the International Space Station, who shared their experiences and discussed the significance of their work in space.